---
import BaseHead from "../components/BaseHead.astro";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
import { SITE_DESCRIPTION, SITE_TITLE } from "../consts";
---

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <BaseHead title={SITE_TITLE} description={SITE_DESCRIPTION} />
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="mx-auto relative">
      <main class="mx-4 text-gray-900">
        <div class="sm:px-8 mb-16">
          <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl lg:px-8">
            <div class="relative px-4 lg:px-12">
              <div class="mb-20">
                <Header title={SITE_TITLE} />
              </div>
              <div>
                <svg
                  class="absolute inset-x-0 top-0 -z-10 h-[64rem] w-full stroke-gray-200 [mask-image:radial-gradient(32rem_32rem_at_center,white,transparent)]"
                  aria-hidden="true"
                >
                  <defs>
                    <pattern
                      id="1f932ae7-37de-4c0a-a8b0-a6e3b4d44b84"
                      width="200"
                      height="200"
                      x="50%"
                      y="-1"
                      patternUnits="userSpaceOnUse"
                    >
                      <path d="M.5 200V.5H200" fill="none"></path>
                    </pattern>
                  </defs>
                  <svg x="50%" y="-1" class="overflow-visible fill-gray-50">
                    <path
                      d="M-200 0h201v201h-201Z M600 0h201v201h-201Z M-400 600h201v201h-201Z M200 800h201v201h-201Z"
                      stroke-width="0"></path>
                  </svg>
                  <rect
                    width="100%"
                    height="100%"
                    stroke-width="0"
                    fill="url(#1f932ae7-37de-4c0a-a8b0-a6e3b4d44b84)"></rect>
                </svg>
                <div
                  class="grid grid-cols-1 gap-y-16 lg:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-rows-[auto_1fr] lg:gap-y-12"
                >
                  <div class="lg:pl-20 flex items-center justify-center">
                    <div class="max-w-xs px-2.5 lg:max-w-md">
                      <img
                        alt="patrick profile picture"
                        loading="lazy"
                        width="800"
                        height="800"
                        decoding="async"
                        data-nimg="1"
                        class="aspect-square rotate-3 rounded-2xl object-cover"
                        sizes="(min-width: 1024px) 32rem, 20rem"
                        src="/assets/images/patrick.jpeg"
                        style="color: transparent;"
                      />
                    </div>
                  </div><div class="lg:order-first lg:row-span-2">
                    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight sm:text-5xl">
                      ðŸ‘‹
                      <span
                        class="ml-1 text-transparent bg-clip-text bg-gradient-to-br from-red-400 to-red-600"
                        >Hi, I'm Patrick.</span
                      >
                    </h1>
                    <div class="mt-6 space-y-7 text-base">
                      <div>
                        <h2
                          class="text-brand-blue text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight"
                        >
                          Short Bio
                        </h2>
                        <p class="text-base text-gray-700 leading-7 mt-2">
                          Patrick, a Principal Software Developer at <a
                            class="underline text-brand-blue"
                            href="https://www.joinoffstreet.com/">Offstreet</a
                          >. Originally from Germany, Patrick moved to Canada in
                          2013 and has since worked with various companies such
                          as Solvera (acquired), Vivvo (acquired), iQmetrix,
                          Outpost Health, Bitovi, and Anedot, while serving both
                          in leadership and individual contributor roles. His
                          focus in the recent years has beenon scalable
                          front-ends. He believes scalable frontends don't just
                          mean that they can serve millions of customers of all
                          walks of life, but are also maintainable, consistent,
                          and iteration proof.
                        </p>
                      </div>
                      <hr />
                      <div>
                        <h2
                          class="text-brand-blue text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight"
                        >
                          All the details
                        </h2>

                        <p class="text-base text-gray-700 leading-7 mt-2">
                          I'm original from Bavaria, Germany ðŸ‡©ðŸ‡ª, but have been
                          living in Canada ðŸ‡¨ðŸ‡¦ since 2013. After finishing my
                          Business Information Systems Diploma I joined the team
                          at <a
                            class="underline text-brand-blue"
                            href="https://solvera.ca/">Solvera</a
                          > (<a
                            class="underline text-brand-blue"
                            href="https://newsroom.accenture.com/news/accenture-acquires-solvera-solutions-to-grow-digital-transformation-capabilities-in-western-canada.htm"
                            >acquired by Accenture</a
                          >), working as a consultant for various government
                          clients. During this time I finished my B. Sc. in
                          Computer Science taking night classes, which I
                          finished in 2018.
                        </p>

                        <p class="text-base text-gray-700 leading-7 mt-2">
                          After 3 years of consulting, I was looking to get
                          involved with a product. I joined <a
                            class="underline text-brand-blue"
                            href="https://www.iqmetrix.com/">iQmetrix</a
                          >, a leader in the Retail management space, before
                          joining <a
                            class="underline text-brand-blue"
                            href="https://www.vivvo.com/">Vivvo</a
                          > (<a
                            class="underline text-brand-blue"
                            href="https://www.newswire.ca/news-releases/converge-technology-solutions-corp-acquires-vivvo-application-studios-ltd--837623472.html"
                            >acquired by Converge Technology Solutions</a
                          >). At this stage, Vivvo was a small start-up with a
                          big vision to transform how every citizen interacts
                          with the government. During this time I served on the
                          Outreach committee as a Co-Chair for the Digital
                          Identification & Authentication Council of Canada (<a
                            class="underline text-brand-blue"
                            href="https://diacc.ca/">DIACC</a
                          >).
                        </p>

                        <p class="text-base text-gray-700 leading-7 mt-2">
                          After leading the architecture of Vivvo's Citizen
                          One's trust platform, I finished my time with Vivvo
                          implementing the backbone of identification and
                          validation that allows an entire province to access
                          their Health Records digitally. From government trust
                          framework to health care startup. 2019, before the
                          pandemic I joined a small team at <a
                            class="underline text-brand-blue"
                            href="https://www.outpost.health/">Outpost Health</a
                          > to build a Digital Health platform focused on providing
                          Digital Health Access and Payments to emerging markets.
                          The platform has been
                          <a
                            class="underline text-brand-blue"
                            href="https://www.unwto.org/news/the-future-is-now-unwto-recognizes-world%E2%80%99s-best-innovators-facing-up-to-covid-19"
                            >recognized by the UNWTO as a leading solution to
                            help accelerate the recovery of tourism in the wake
                            of the pandemic.</a
                          >
                        </p>

                        <p class="text-base text-gray-700 leading-7 mt-2">
                          Taking a break from start-ups, I joined <a
                            class="underline text-brand-blue"
                            href="https://www.bitovi.com/">Bitovi</a
                          >, where I became the Co-Director of the React
                          department shortly after. My contributions were split
                          between growing the React department and leading and
                          working with teams at Fortune 500 companies.
                        </p>

                        <p class="text-base text-gray-700 leading-7 mt-2">
                          As much as I enjoy consulting, I knew my heart was in
                          building products. I joined <a
                            class="underline text-brand-blue"
                            href="https://www.anedot.com/">Anedot</a
                          >, an online donation platform with over $1B in
                          transaction volume. During my time there, I was able
                          to lead the complete rewrite of a 10+ year old RoR
                          application into a React-based frontend.
                        </p>

                        <p class="text-base text-gray-700 leading-7 mt-2">
                          After being involved in many complete rewrites, design
                          system creations, and greenfield projects, I saw an
                          opportunity to create a software studio that would
                          helps startups to move fast, and large corporations
                          and government entities to move with confidence. Thus,
                          I founded Kollektiv Software Studio Inc. Kollektiv
                          Software Studio has contributed to government
                          agencies, delivered consulting services, and acted as
                          an early-stage investor.
                        </p>
